# Security-critical posture — any change must be explicitly reviewed.
#
# This file declares ownership. Enforcement requires the branch-protection rule
# "Require review from Code Owners" on `main` (Settings → Branches → main → Require
# a pull request before merging → Require review from Code Owners). Without that
# toggle, this file is documentary, not enforcing.
#
# Pair with `scripts/check-template.sh` section 6 (posture invariants) — CODEOWNERS
# is the review-time layer; section 6 is the CI-time layer. Together they close the
# silent-revert risk class (an unrebased branch whose PR diff looks like deletions of
# deny-list / redaction lines).

.gitignore                @mjvacas
SECURITY.md               @mjvacas
.claude/settings.json     @mjvacas
.claude/hooks/            @mjvacas
scripts/check-template.sh @mjvacas
scripts/audit-config.sh   @mjvacas
